    "discriminators": [
     "VEGETATION as a CLASS has a real signature - a dry, bright, broadband, HF-dominated stochastic RUSTLE: dense unresolvable micro-events, very high zero_crossings_per_second, high spectral_flatness, high centroid, almost no energy below 200 Hz, low crest factor. That is measurable, and it usefully rules out tonal, impulsive and low-frequency material. The SUBCATEGORIES, however, are botany.",
     "GRASS vs LEAVES is not a DSP-decidable boundary, and no honest number can be written for it. Both are the same bright, dry, stochastic rustle produced by the same mechanism - thin cellulose sheets sliding over each other - and the spectra overlap almost completely. Any threshold between them would be a fabrication. semantic_only for both; the synonyms decide.",
     "The only whisper of a tendency - blades of grass are lighter than a dead leaf, so the micro-events are finer and the centroid sits marginally higher - is well inside the variance caused by moisture, mic distance and how hard the Foley artist grabbed the handful. It is encoded as a hair of centroid difference and is not worth trusting.",
     "What the class priors DO buy: the rustle signature reliably rules out tonal, impulsive and low-frequency candidates. That is real pruning value even though the sibling boundary is not.",
     "Confusable on signal with CLOTH, PAPER, DIRT_SAND and FIRE crackle - all bright, dry, dense textures."
    ],
    "confusable_with": [
     "VEGELeaf",
     "VEGEMisc",
     "CLOTHMisc",
     "DIRTMisc"
    ]
