    "discriminators": [
     "VEGETATION as a CLASS has a real signature - a dry, bright, broadband, HF-dominated stochastic RUSTLE: dense unresolvable micro-events, very high zero_crossings_per_second, high spectral_flatness, high centroid, almost no energy below 200 Hz, low crest factor. That is measurable, and it usefully rules out tonal, impulsive and low-frequency material. The SUBCATEGORIES, however, are botany.",
     "The canonical rustle, and the reference point for the whole category: dry leaves are the textbook bright broadband dense texture. But LEAVES vs GRASS vs the rustling half of TREE is botany, not acoustics - the same physics, the same spectrum. semantic_only; the synonyms decide.",
     "A jump into a leaf pile (from the explanation) is a single big burst of the same texture: expect a fast attack and a long decaying tail on top of the texture priors, which stretches crest_factor upward.",
     "Confusable on signal with CLOTH, PAPER and FIRE crackle. FIRE is distinguished by sparse, sharp, high-crest pops on top of a HISS floor; a rustle has no hiss bed."
